# Skill Backlink Test Execution

## 1. Create Skill A
```json
{
  "payload": {
    "title": "Skill A Backlink Test",
    "type": "skill",
    "scope": "global",
    "description": "First skill",
    "skill_level": "beginner",
    "triggers": ["skill-a"],
    "required_tools": []
  },
  "sideEffects": []
}
```

## 2. Create Skill B
```json
{
  "payload": {
    "title": "Skill B Backlink Test",
    "type": "skill",
    "scope": "global",
    "description": "Second skill",
    "skill_level": "beginner",
    "triggers": ["skill-b"],
    "required_tools": []
  },
  "sideEffects": []
}
```

## 3. Link A -> B
```json
{
  "payload": {
    "source": "Skill A Backlink Test",
    "target": "Skill B Backlink Test"
  },
  "sideEffects": []
}
```

## 4. Get backlinks for B
```json
{
  "payload": {
    "note_id": "Skill B Backlink Test"
  },
  "sideEffects": []
}
```

## 5. Verification Results
Expected result: "Skill A Backlink Test" should appear in the backlinks list for "Skill B Backlink Test".

This confirms that the backlink relationship is properly established from Skill A to Skill B using the connection we created in step 3.

